                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, very irregular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red (brilliant vermillion)</seg>
                        Scribe: ʾIyasu. ʾIyasu is mentioned
                        as the scribe on <locus target="#118ra">118ra</locus> (s.
                           colophon).<date>18th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra (Māryām); name of the protagonist; name
                           of the scribe; name of the commissioner and his children; some initial
                           lines in Text I (e.g., fol. 15rb); a few lines alternating with black
                           lines on the incipit page of Text II; incipits of miracles; elements of
                           the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Distinctive
                        features:</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> - ጵ has the 6th order marker set up on
                        the vertical stroke at the top, oriented to the left (e.g., <locus target="#1ra">1ra</locus> l.3, 17ra
                        l.9)</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"> - ፮ is with the loop open, looking
                        like “compressed” ፯ (e.g., <locus target="#101vb">101vb</locus> l.2 and
                        quire mark on <locus target="#47vb">47vb</locus>).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Omitted letters or words written interlineally: e.g., fols. 34va, 36ra, 36vb, 65va, 126ra, 134ra. - Erasures marked by thin parallel lines (in black): e.g., fols. 37rb, 68vb, 69ra, 84vb, 97rb. - Writing exercises (?) in the margins of fols 76v and 77r. - Crude notes and/or drawings in pen or in pencil: e.g., fols. 1r, 5r, 63v, 64v, 74r, 136v, 137r. - <locus target="#137rb">Fol.  137rb</locus>: crude ornamental band (?)</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
